cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for unsupervised learning of deep neural networks through combining clustering and representation learning. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with image representations. The method also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it uses cross-entropy minimization. Finally, the use of the Sinkhorn-Knopp algorithm suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
